<br>
However, it makes no sense for them to give us this at all.  It should be nerfed.  Hp and ANY increase in tanking are in the domain of melee, not robe wearers.  When you constantly blur the differences between the classes you make a more homogenous game where everyone begins to fill a more and more similiar role.  The entire argument of &quot;balance&quot; in eq is flawed from the player point of view.  Balance does not imply identical capability and performance in all situations.  It should impy a world where everyone has uses, everyone has strengths and everyone has weeknesses, and all these pro's and con's exist in fairly similiar NET quantities.  Balance in the commonly used sense in EQ makes for the eventuality of a boring game with no distinguishable classes.  (an obvious extreme).<br>
<br>
If you don't like that argument, here's another attempt at describing why we shouldnt have ND:<br>
<br>
Now EVERY single class has ND.  That effectively makes ND worthless.  The only thing that distinguishes classes is the difference between them.  By giving a 10% increase to hitpoints ACROSS THE BOARD for all classes you hve effectively done nothing but allow for mobs to hit 10% harder.  The game is not changed at all.  The characters gain nothing.  It is static.  Give hp to warriors and tanks.  Give mana to casters... that makes for an improvement in those classes relative to each other.  Giving EVERYONE 10% more hp does NOTHING.<br>
<br>
If you feel the need to add to our aa pools, give us a &quot;mental Durability&quot; that gives us 10% more mana, or a &quot;Mental Stability&quot; that increases our specialization % when we make the check.  But don't stack us up in line with melee.  I'm a caster, I wan't that distinction. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=315013">Shard Elay</a>
